originalText.text:
After 2 years of cleaning, X-rays, 180, treatment, implant, crown across multiple departments and really trying my hardest to work with the staff, this place is TERRIBLE. The billing and admin is ran by incompetent people locked behind a screen. Ground floor checking / billing, 2S admin or 5th admin or office staff can only tell you what you owe but never what you are being charged for nor the details nor the treatment plans associated to it. The online portal has no information.  I have signed so many ‚Äúupdated‚Äù treatment plans even while on the dentist chair and with treatment in progress. Bills are always very uncertain. I came in for one specific condition: one implant. It never changed but the bill and the treatment kept on changing. At the end this didn‚Äôt cost less than a regular dentist despite what is advertised.

When a complaint arises, they advise to contact the patient advocacy. The pamphlet mentioned that one can visit their office but no one is ever there. If you try calling, it will give you a voice mail and no luck to leave a voice mail. When sending a form via the contact form for each floor or service, just don‚Äôt expect an answer and if you are lucky they may call you back but if you miss the call, then good luck trying to contact them again.

originalText.text: If you have an actual dental emergency. don't even bother. The registration process takes more than 1 hour and 15 mins  before you even get to the floor to see an actual dentist (student) once you get to the floor they assigned to you. You have to wait again until you are seen on that floor.  now the receptionist can't give you an actual wait time due to the fact that she has so many papers she doesn't even want to look to see if  you have anyone in front of you. Be aware that time is not going to be on your side.

originalText.text: Across the board, every staff member, including student doctors and supervising doctors are very professional, well informed and courteous. Great prices as well. I recommend NYCD to everyone who wants great dental care results. Sincerely, Jorge Rodriguez.
